4) Reverse Only Words with Even Length

  What You are Given:

A sentence with multiple words separated by spaces.

  What You Must Do:

 Check each word.
 If the word length is even â†’ reverse the word.
 If the word length is odd â†’ keep it as it is.
 Keep all spaces and word positions EXACTLY the same.

  Restrictions:

âŒ No loops (no `for`, `while`)
âŒ No regex
 You can only use:

 `.trim()`
 `.split(" ")`
 `.map(...)`
 `.join(" ")`
 `.length`

  Output:

Return the final transformed sentence.

---

  SIMPLE LOGIC (Step-by-Step)

1ï¸âƒ£ Split the sentence into words.
2ï¸âƒ£ For each word:

 If `word.length % 2 == 0` â†’ reverse it.
 Else â†’ keep it unchanged.
  3ï¸âƒ£ Join the words back into a sentence.

---

  INPUT & OUTPUT EXAMPLES

  Example 1

Input:

```
"Hello world"
```

Word lengths:

 Hello â†’ 5 (odd) â†’ keep
 world â†’ 5 (odd) â†’ keep

Output:

```
"Hello world"
```

 No changes.

---

  Example 2

Input:

```
"Hi John Doe"
```

Words:

 Hi â†’ 2 (even) â†’ reverse â†’ "iH"
 John â†’ 4 (even) â†’ reverse â†’ "nhoJ"
 Doe â†’ 3 (odd) â†’ keep

Output:

```
"iH nhoJ Doe"
```

---

  Example 3

Input:

```
"Time to code"
```

Words:

 Time â†’ 4 (even) â†’ "emiT"
 to â†’ 2 (even) â†’ "ot"
 code â†’ 4 (even) â†’ "edoc"

Output:

```
"emiT ot edoc"
```

---

  Example 4 (spaces must stay same!)

Input:

```
"Play  and fun"
```

Words:

 Play â†’ 4 (even) â†’ "yalP"
 and â†’ 3 (odd) â†’ keep
 fun â†’ 3 (odd) â†’ keep

Output:

```
"yalP  and fun"
```

